<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <%- include("../../parts/head") %>
</head>

<body class="d-flex flex-column min-vh-100 bg-wyrd-default">

    <!-- Navbar -->
    <%- include("../../parts/navbar") %>

        <!-- Content -->
        <div class="container min-vh-100 bg-light shadow-lg border-start border-end border-dark-subtle">
            <div class="container-content">
                <!-- Hero Image -->
                <div class="row mb-3">
                    <div class="col">
                        <h3 class="lora-semibold">Society</h3>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row gap-3">
                    <div class="col-md">
                        <p>
                            Before the world had borders, kingdoms, or names, there was Limbo — an endless,
                            formless void where thought, matter, spirit, and time had not yet separated.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            From that vast and unknowable beginning emerged the Eternals, four timeless beings who
                            embodied the fundamental truths of existence.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Foundation gave substance to creation, shaping the physical world and all that endures
                            within it. Spirit awakened essence, memory, and identity, breathing meaning into things.
                            Harmony established order, law, and the patterns that bind reality together, while
                            Discord introduced change, freedom, and endless possibility.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Together, the Eternals transformed Limbo into a living universe brimming with life in all
                            its forms. Their ancient influence still echoes through every corner of creation, though few
                            claim to understand their true nature.
                        </p>
                        <h6 class="lora-semibold">The Mortal Realm</h6>
                        <p>
                            The Mortal Realm formed where the primoridal spark found balance, a place of change, death,
                            memory, and choice. As the world matured and life evolved, the New Gods rose to
                            prominence. Unlike their distant and apathetic forerunners, these deities walked among
                            mortals, forged kingdoms, taught crafts, inspired faiths, and waged wars in their own names.
                            Temples honor
                            them, priests invoke them, and heroes trace their bloodlines to their legendary deeds.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Beyond the mortal world lie countless realms shaped by the powers that dwell within them.
                            The radiant heavens, the infernal depths, elemental domains, spirit realms, and stranger
                            places all exist alongside one another, separated less by distance than by the boundaries of
                            reality itself. Most people know the divine through festivals, houses of worship, rites of
                            passage, temple courts, and local legends.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Adventurers encounter the divine more directly. They may
                            recover relics from ancient ruins, bargain with spirits in haunted forests, descend into
                            places where the Infernal Depths bleed into the earth, and uncover truths that the clergy
                            would rather keep buried.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md">
                        <div class="row mb-3">
                            <img class="img-fluid object-fit-cover" src="/img/society.png" />
                        </div>
                        <div class="row">
                            <!-- Content here -->
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

</body>

</html>